{
  "id": 4740780497043456,
  "name": "CSS typed arithmetic",
  "summary": "Typed arithmetic allows to write expressions in CSS such a calc(10em / 1px) or calc(20% / 0.5em * 1px) which is useful for e.g. typography, as it allows to convert typed value into an untyped one and reuse it for number accepting properties or futher multiply the unitless value by some other type to e.g. cast from pixels to degrees.",
